<body>
    <div class="terms-container">
        <h1>YageCoin Staking Terms & Conditions</h1>
        
        <p><strong>Last Updated:</strong> [Current Date]</p>
        
        <div class="warning">
            <strong>⚠️ IMPORTANT:</strong> Please read these Staking Terms carefully before participating in any staking activities. By staking tokens, you acknowledge and accept all risks outlined below.
        </div>

        <h2>1. Definition of Staking</h2>
        <p>Staking refers to the process of locking your YGCT or YGC tokens in our platform for a specified period to receive rewards. Staking is a utility feature of our tokens, NOT an investment contract or security offering.</p>

        <h2>2. Token Utility</h2>
        <p>YGCT and YGC are utility tokens that provide:</p>
        <ul>
            <li>Platform fee discounts</li>
            <li>Cashback multipliers</li>
            <li>Access to premium features</li>
            <li>Governance participation (future)</li>
            <li>Reward accumulation through staking</li>
        </ul>
        <p><strong>They are NOT:</strong> Securities, investment contracts, equity, profit-sharing instruments, or guaranteed stores of value.</p>

        <h2>3. Staking Tiers and APY</h2>
        
        <h3>3.1 YGCT Staking Tiers:</h3>
        <ul>
            <li><strong>Flexible:</strong> 15% APY, no lock period</li>
            <li><strong>Silver:</strong> 30% APY, 30-day lock</li>
            <li><strong>Gold:</strong> 50% APY, 90-day lock</li>
            <li><strong>Diamond:</strong> 100% APY, 180-day lock</li>
        </ul>

        <h3>3.2 YGC Staking Tiers:</h3>
        <ul>
            <li><strong>Degen:</strong> 25% APY, no lock period</li>
            <li><strong>Moon Chaser:</strong> 69% APY, 30-day lock</li>
            <li><strong>Diamond Hands:</strong> 420% APY, 90-day lock</li>
        </ul>

        <h3>3.3 APY Disclaimer:</h3>
        <p><strong>APY rates are VARIABLE and NOT GUARANTEED.</strong> We reserve the right to adjust APY rates at any time based on:</p>
        <ul>
            <li>Platform revenue and sustainability</li>
            <li>Token supply and demand</li>
            <li>Market conditions</li>
            <li>Total Value Locked (TVL)</li>
        </ul>
        <p>Changes to APY may apply to new stakes immediately and to existing stakes at our discretion with notice.</p>

        <h2>4. Lock Periods</h2>
        
        <h3>4.1 Locked Stakes:</h3>
        <p>When you choose a locked tier (Silver, Gold, Diamond for YGCT; Moon Chaser, Diamond Hands for YGC), your tokens are locked for the specified period. During this time:</p>
        <ul>
            <li>You CANNOT withdraw your staked tokens</li>
            <li>Tokens are inaccessible until lock period ends</li>
            <li>No emergency withdrawal option</li>
            <li>Early unstaking results in penalties (see section 5)</li>
        </ul>

        <h3>4.2 Flexible Stakes:</h3>
        <p>Flexible tier allows withdrawal at any time without penalties, but offers lower APY.</p>

        <h2>5. Early Unstaking Penalties</h2>
        <p>If you request early unstaking from a locked tier:</p>
        <ul>
            <li><strong>Penalty Fee:</strong> 10% of staked principal</li>
            <li><strong>Forfeited Rewards:</strong> All accumulated rewards are lost</li>
            <li><strong>Processing Time:</strong> 7-14 days for manual review</li>
        </ul>
        <p><strong>We strongly discourage early unstaking.</strong> Only stake amounts you can afford to lock for the full period.</p>

        <h2>6. Rewards Calculation and Distribution</h2>
        
        <h3>6.1 How Rewards Work:</h3>
        <p>Rewards = (Staked Amount × APY) / 365 days</p>
        <p>Rewards accumulate daily from the moment your stake is activated.</p>

        <h3>6.2 Distribution Schedule:</h3>
        <ul>
            <li>Rewards calculated daily</li>
            <li>Distribution occurs weekly or monthly</li>
            <li>Minimum claimable amount: 1 token</li>
            <li>Rewards sent directly to your wallet</li>
        </ul>

        <h3>6.3 Reward Source:</h3>
        <p>Staking rewards come from:</p>
        <ul>
            <li>Platform transaction fees (swap/bridge commissions)</li>
            <li>Token allocation reserves for staking incentives</li>
            <li>Ecosystem growth initiatives</li>
        </ul>
        <p>Rewards are sustainable as they're tied to real platform revenue and usage.</p>

        <h2>7. Risks</h2>
        
        <div class="warning">
            <h3>⚠️ YOU ACKNOWLEDGE THE FOLLOWING RISKS:</h3>
        </div>

        <h3>7.1 Token Price Volatility:</h3>
        <ul>
            <li>Token prices can fluctuate dramatically</li>
            <li>You may lose significant value even while earning rewards</li>
            <li>Example: 50% APY but token drops 60% = net loss</li>
            <li>Staking rewards DO NOT compensate for price decreases</li>
        </ul>

        <h3>7.2 Smart Contract Risk:</h3>
        <ul>
            <li>Smart contracts may contain bugs or vulnerabilities</li>
            <li>Hacks or exploits could result in total loss</li>
            <li>We conduct security reviews but cannot guarantee 100% security</li>
            <li>DeFi protocols have been hacked historically</li>
        </ul>

        <h3>7.3 Liquidity Risk:</h3>
        <ul>
            <li>During lock period, you cannot access your tokens</li>
            <li>You cannot sell even if price is dropping</li>
            <li>Emergency situations (medical, financial) don't bypass lock</li>
        </ul>

        <h3>7.4 Regulatory Risk:</h3>
        <ul>
            <li>Cryptocurrency regulations are evolving</li>
            <li>Future laws may restrict or prohibit staking</li>
            <li>We may need to discontinue service in certain jurisdictions</li>
            <li>Tax implications vary by country - consult tax advisor</li>
        </ul>

        <h3>7.5 Platform Risk:</h3>
        <ul>
            <li>YageCoin platform may cease operations</li>
            <li>Technical failures could delay or prevent withdrawals</li>
            <li>We're not liable for losses due to platform issues</li>
        </ul>

        <h3>7.6 Impermanent Loss:</h3>
        <p>While staking itself doesn't cause impermanent loss, if you're staking LP tokens or comparing to other DeFi strategies, opportunity cost is real.</p>

        <h2>8. Eligibility and Restrictions</h2>
        
        <h3>8.1 Who Can Stake:</h3>
        <ul>
            <li>Must be 18+ years old</li>
            <li>Cryptocurrency must be legal in your jurisdiction</li>
            <li>Not a resident of prohibited countries (see main Terms)</li>
            <li>Comply with local tax and reporting requirements</li>
        </ul>

        <h3>8.2 Minimum Stakes:</h3>
        <ul>
            <li>YGCT: 100 tokens minimum</li>
            <li>YGC: 1,000 tokens minimum</li>
        </ul>

        <h3>8.3 Maximum Stakes:</h3>
        <p>No maximum, but extremely large stakes may be subject to additional verification.</p>

        <h2>9. How to Stake</h2>
        
        <h3>9.1 Process:</h3>
        <ol>
            <li>Connect Web3 wallet (MetaMask, etc.)</li>
            <li>Choose token (YGCT or YGC)</li>
            <li>Select tier and lock period</li>
            <li>Send tokens to staking address provided</li>
            <li>Submit transaction hash for verification</li>
            <li>Wait 24-48 hours for activation</li>
            <li>Rewards begin accumulating after activation</li>
        </ol>

        <h3>9.2 Verification:</h3>
        <p>We manually verify all stake transactions to prevent fraud. This means:</p>
        <ul>
            <li>Stakes are not instant</li>
            <li>24-48 hour activation period</li>
            <li>We check transaction hash on blockchain</li>
            <li>Invalid transactions are rejected</li>
        </ul>

        <h2>10. Withdrawal and Unstaking</h2>
        
        <h3>10.1 Normal Unstaking:</h3>
        <ul>
            <li>Request unstaking via dashboard</li>
            <li>For locked tiers: Only available after lock period ends</li>
            <li>For flexible tier: Available anytime</li>
            <li>Processing time: 3-7 days</li>
            <li>Receive principal + unclaimed rewards</li>
        </ul>

        <h3>10.2 Claiming Rewards Only:</h3>
        <ul>
            <li>Claim accumulated rewards without unstaking</li>
            <li>Available weekly or upon request</li>
            <li>Minimum claim: 1 token</li>
            <li>Gas fees may apply</li>
        </ul>

        <h2>11. Modifications to Staking Program</h2>
        <p>We reserve the right to:</p>
        <ul>
            <li>Adjust APY rates with notice</li>
            <li>Add or remove staking tiers</li>
            <li>Change lock periods for new stakes</li>
            <li>Modify reward distribution schedule</li>
            <li>Discontinue staking program (with transition period)</li>
        </ul>
        <p><strong>Existing stakes:</strong> We will honor original terms for existing stakes whenever possible, but reserve right to make changes if necessary for platform sustainability.</p>

        <h2>12. Tax Obligations</h2>
        <p>YOU are solely responsible for:</p>
        <ul>
            <li>Determining tax implications in your jurisdiction</li>
            <li>Reporting staking rewards as income (if required)</li>
            <li>Paying capital gains tax on token appreciation</li>
            <li>Maintaining records of all transactions</li>
            <li>Filing appropriate tax forms</li>
        </ul>
        <p><strong>We do not provide tax advice.</strong> Consult a tax professional familiar with cryptocurrency.</p>

        <h2>13. No Financial Advice</h2>
        <div class="warning">
            <p><strong>CRITICAL DISCLAIMER:</strong></p>
            <p>Staking YGCT/YGC is NOT financial advice. We do NOT recommend staking as an investment. Staking is a utility feature for token holders who want platform benefits and are willing to accept the risks.</p>
            <p>Do NOT stake:</p>
            <ul>
                <li>Money you cannot afford to lose</li>
                <li>Emergency funds</li>
                <li>Borrowed money</li>
                <li>Retirement savings</li>
            </ul>
        </div>

        <h2>14. Limitation of Liability</h2>
        <p>TO THE MAXIMUM EXTENT PERMITTED BY LAW:</p>
        <ul>
            <li>We are NOT liable for token price losses</li>
            <li>We are NOT liable for smart contract failures</li>
            <li>We are NOT liable for blockchain network issues</li>
            <li>We are NOT liable for opportunity costs</li>
            <li>We are NOT liable for tax penalties</li>
            <li>Total liability limited to amount you staked (not including lost rewards or value)</li>
